main event: A bright light was observed by a radar operator travelling northeast horizontally across the sky in Silver Spring, Maryland on November 11, 1962.
interesting points: The sighting was reported to the Air Force but not investigated at the time due to the delay in notification.
The Air Force's Project Blue Book classified the sighting as 'Insufficient Data - Possibly Balloon, Possibly Aircraft, Possibly Astronomical'.
The Air Force requested additional information about the sighting, including any photographs that may have been taken.
The sighting was reported to the 4th District Office of Special Investigations (OSI) on April 11, 1963, several months after the actual incident.
The report indicates that a time exposure photograph was allegedly made of the UFO, but it is unclear if this photograph was ever provided to the Air Force.
photographs: possibly, but not received by the Air Force
